docs.abstract: Several towns with large ultra-Orthodox Jewish populations are seeing coronavirus case rates that are among the highest in New York.
docs.snippet: Several towns with large ultra-Orthodox Jewish populations are seeing coronavirus case rates that are among the highest in New York.
docs.lead_paragraph: PALM TREE, N.Y. — In this town of 26,000 residents, where life revolves around family, religious services and prayer, the percentage of coronavirus tests coming back positive is at least 15 percent, among the highest in New York. There are more than 200 active cases, enough to place this Orthodox Jewish community northwest of New York City into a state-ordered “red zone” with strict new restrictions on synagogue capacity and public gatherings.

headline.main: 15% of Virus Tests Are Positive, and Few Wear Masks in One Orthodox Suburb
headline.print_headline: Orthodox Suburbs See Uptick, but Few Masks
